{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b53ead63-7111-419e-bf7e-cf5b3c46e5ec","content":"No worries — I don't need the file to answer this. Here's how to configure it:\n\nCreate `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- **`command`/`args`** — runs `dotnet run` pointing at your project.\n- Make sure your server uses **stdio transport** (not HTTP/SSE). The C# MCP SDK defaults to this with `WithStdioServerTransport()`.\n\nAfter saving, open the Copilot chat panel in agent mode — it will auto-discover the server and its tools.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8ae1a33f-cffb-4514-b3b4-45559b20b931","outputTokens":237},"id":"f69225f7-6b3b-4525-a1c6-c6d845655f52","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:54:10.121Z","parentId":"5671035a-4b1d-4b8c-a92c-917577590bb5"}
